### parseBackslash() {#abba3a1b37c8d40cefcab729ee016441d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static size&#95;t parseBackslash (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Src, size&#95;t I, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallstring">SmallString</a>&lt; 128 &gt; &amp; Token)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Backslashes are interpreted in a rather complicated way in the Windows-style command line, because backslashes are used both to separate path and to escape double quote.

This method consumes runs of backslashes as well as the following double quote if it&#39;s escaped.


<ul>
<li>If an even number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and the last double quote remains unconsumed. The double quote will later be interpreted as the start or end of a quoted string in the main loop outside of this function.</li>
<li>If an odd number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and a double quote is output for the last pair of backslash-double quote. The double quote is consumed in this case.</li>
<li>Otherwise, backslashes are interpreted literally.</li>
</ul>

Definition at line <a href="#l00899">899</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/commandline-cpp">CommandLine.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00882" /><CodeLine lineNumber="882"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Backslashes are interpreted in a rather complicated way in the Windows-style</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00883" /><CodeLine lineNumber="883"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// command line, because backslashes are used both to separate path and to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00884" /><CodeLine lineNumber="884"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// escape double quote. This method consumes runs of backslashes as well as the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00885" /><CodeLine lineNumber="885"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// following double quote if it&#39;s escaped.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00886" /><CodeLine lineNumber="886"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="887"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  &#42; If an even number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00888" /><CodeLine lineNumber="888"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and the last double</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="889"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    quote remains unconsumed. The double quote will later be interpreted as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00890" /><CodeLine lineNumber="890"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    the start or end of a quoted string in the main loop outside of this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="892"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  &#42; If an odd number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="894"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and a double quote is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="895"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    output for the last pair of backslash-double quote. The double quote is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="896"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    consumed in this case.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  &#42; Otherwise, backslashes are interpreted literally.</span></CodeLine>
